{"id": "bbs5kp", "title": "$BIOAQ restructuring. #YOLO Play of the Year", "selftext": "$BIOAQ BioAmber ran a Bio-Succinic Acid plant built in 2015 for $140M. Bio-SA is a building block chemical derived from feedstock fermented by patented yeasts.\n\n&amp;#x200B;\n\nThe company filed for Ch 11 (5/8/18), which was later dismissed and filed as Ch 15 with CCAA as foreign main proceedings, PWC overseeing as court-appointed monitor.\n\n&amp;#x200B;\n\nThis plant supposedly sold for $4.3M in CCAA (Canada) proceedings (10/22/18). \n\nFair market value of the plant in liquidation scenario appraised at CAD $70-$95M per Nexant (5/22/18, appraisal ordered by PWC).\n\n[https://www.theobserver.ca/news/local-news/sale-of-sarnia-bioamber-plant-completed](https://www.theobserver.ca/news/local-news/sale-of-sarnia-bioamber-plant-completed)\n\n&amp;#x200B;\n\nAlthough the plant sold, the transaction remains ongoing. The court ordered stay has been extended multiple times despite transaction closing almost 6 months ago.\n\n[https://www.pwc.com/ca/en/services/insolvency-assignments/bioamber/court-motions-and-orders.html](https://www.pwc.com/ca/en/services/insolvency-assignments/bioamber/court-motions-and-orders.html)\n\n&amp;#x200B;\n\n..it's starting to look like a two-step acquisition via IRC \u00a7368(a)(1)(D) in order for the acquirer to utilize tax attributes.\n\n[https://www.law.cornell.edu/uscode/text/26/368](https://www.law.cornell.edu/uscode/text/26/368)\n\n&amp;#x200B;\n\nBoth PWC and Blakes (BioAmber's Canadian legal counsel) have named this transaction a restructuring.\n\n&amp;#x200B;\n\n&amp;#x200B;\n\nLots of reasons why shares may stay alive :\n\n&amp;#x200B;\n\n$320M in NOLs\n\n&amp;#x200B;\n\n$77.6M in deferred tax assets (2017)\n\n&amp;#x200B;\n\n&amp;#x200B;\n\nA 15 year off-take agreement with Vinmar worth $3B \n\n[https://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/bioamber-signs-take-or-pay-contract-for-three-bio-succinic-acid-plants-266099031.html](https://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/bioamber-signs-take-or-pay-contract-for-three-bio-succinic-acid-plants-266099031.html)\n\n&amp;#x200B;\n\nAn agreement with CJ Cheljedang retrofitting existing plants and contemplating a (70/30) JV with future plants.\n\n[https://content.edgar-online.com/ExternalLink/EDGAR/0001564590-18-007185.html?hash=8f0bf5a1898f4c79d9226b6f646497e27ec7847fff8b6c7c3352673f9ffb9286&amp;dest=BIOA-EX1065\\_6\\_HTM#BIOA-EX1065\\_6\\_HTM](https://content.edgar-online.com/ExternalLink/EDGAR/0001564590-18-007185.html?hash=8f0bf5a1898f4c79d9226b6f646497e27ec7847fff8b6c7c3352673f9ffb9286&amp;dest=BIOA-EX1065_6_HTM#BIOA-EX1065_6_HTM)\n\n&amp;#x200B;\n\nLicenses &amp; Agreements required to run the plant and fulfill off-take agreement are tied to BioAmber Inc. ($BIOAQ) \n\n[https://www.sec.gov/Archives/edgar/data/1534287/000156459016014867/bioa-ex1061\\_303.htm](https://www.sec.gov/Archives/edgar/data/1534287/000156459016014867/bioa-ex1061_303.htm) \n\n[https://www.sec.gov/Archives/edgar/data/1534287/000119312513148318/d442100dex1033.htm](https://www.sec.gov/Archives/edgar/data/1534287/000119312513148318/d442100dex1033.htm)\n\n&amp;#x200B;\n\nThe purchaser (a JV between LCY Chemical &amp; Visolis) also purchased the plans &amp; permits for a second plant which require said licenses &amp; agreements.\n\n&amp;#x200B;\n\nLCY Chemical was just acquired by KKR for $1.5B on 1/31/19. \n\n[http://www.taipeitimes.com/News/biz/archives/2019/01/31/2003708947](http://www.taipeitimes.com/News/biz/archives/2019/01/31/2003708947)\n\n&amp;#x200B;\n\nVisolis was seeded by Royal DSM, and retains a branch office on the same campus as DSM.\n\n&amp;#x200B;\n\nMost likely KKR is providing financing for $BIOAQ restructuring and future plants in order to expand their recent acquisition of LCY Chemical.\n\n&amp;#x200B;\n\nVery big names in the mix: KKR, LCY, DSM, Cargill, Vinmar, CJ Cheljedang\n\n&amp;#x200B;\n\nTotal lottery play but the more I read, the more I like the odds.\n\n&amp;#x200B;\n\n\\#YOLO", "created_utc": 1554934319, "permalink": "/r/wallstreetbets/comments/bbs5kp/bioaq_restructuring_yolo_play_of_the_year/", "is_self": true}